    {
      "id": "sybil_1_listing_1",
      "firm_id": "sybil_1",
      "description": "Hey there! I'm parting ways with my absolute pride and joy. Honestly, you won\u2019t find another one like this\u2014it looks and drives like it just rolled off the showroom floor! I\u2019ve babied this car since day one, always kept it garaged, and kept up with every single service. It\u2019s in truly pristine condition and ready for a new home. Come take a look, you're going to love it!",
      "price": 44500.0,
      "reputation": 0.8,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This concours-level example features a blueprint-balanced, naturally aspirated inline-six powerplant paired with a short-throw six-speed manual transaxle. The chassis exhibits zero fatigue, retaining factory-spec torsional rigidity and augmented by a multi-link rear suspension with upgraded monotube dampers. Performance is optimized via a mechanical limited-slip differential and four-piston monobloc calipers clamping cross-drilled rotors. Every bushing, seal, and fluid line remains in impeccable condition, ensuring a direct and communicative steering rack free of play. The aerodynamic profile is preserved with original paint depth and flawless underbody shielding, representing a peak-era analog driving experience with an unblemished service history.",
      "price": 48750.0,
      "reputation": 0.8,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_3_listing_3",
      "firm_id": "sybil_3",
      "description": "Mint condition. Single owner. Zero accidents. Garage stored. Maintenance records included. Clean title.",
      "price": 48500.0,
      "reputation": 0.7,
